inladen and leaving it at that you make a martyr out of him and all of those children celebrating in the streets will grow up to be just like him.  We have tried to work things out diplomaticaly.  Jimmy Carter tried, Bill Clinton certainly tried and they still spit in our face.  They do not understand nor acknowledge pascifism, so that is no longer an option.  We must make such an indelible impression on their psyche that these actions are no longer an option for them.  Sad to say it, but the Japanese during WWII had a similar attitude as these terrorists and countries that are harboring and financing these terrorists.  After giving the Japanese 3 days notice of our intentions of dropping the bomb they chose not to evacuate, we dropped.  We gave them another chance for surrender, they refused, we dropped.  Finally after such a show of force had been shown them that they understood the war was finally over.  Japan has become a better place for that and have thrown away all their ideals of imperialism and conquest since.  In no way am I advocating nukes but am just using this as an example of the way these people think and react.  They have thrown down the guantlet and forced us to make a choice, do we do what it takes to secure our way of life that 280 million Americans hold dear, or do we slap their wrists and wait to defend ourselfs against the next attack on us.  It's as simple as that, make your choice, the line has been drawn in the sand.  And for all you overseas people that criticize our actions and future actions, you have no right because you are not in a position where you very way of life is threatened. <p><table><tr><td style="filter:glow(color=green strength=5);font-family:papyrus;font-weight: BOLD;font-size:'10pt'">Goldeneyes<Br><i>Revealed</i></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubarshproudgut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarshProud