ize were were in the top 3 strategic targets within the U.S. during the Cold War?  Ignorance is no excuse and can be lethal.<br><br>I suppose some of you would prefer a passive response.  Let me just say that if there is no retaliation we give a license to other terrorists to repeat this episode.  Your passivity would cause the deaths of tens more thousand Americans over the next few years.  Sometimes you have to choose the lesser of two evils:  Let many more Americans get killed or chase down and annihilate military targets, possibly hurting some late-running civilians of another country.<br><br>The choice is not a difficult one to make.  Don't over-think it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udeagol666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deagol666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Junior Member</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/15/01 3:02:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> To the parties responsible for the 911 attacks:</span><hr size=1> Yeah i agree with you Garryck, perhaps the amount of civilian casualties will be way lower, but you still got military casualties to deal with.<br>Taking over Afghan is going to be a helluva lot of work, and many american soldiers will perish. Afghan terrain makes it hard to use any machinery in there, tanks, artillery, whatever. Only thing you have left is planes, which are quite hard to use because of all the rocky slopes and high mountains, and good ole infantry. <br>They are going to need one hell of a lot of mountain climing experience to wage war in Afghan, not to mention that their opposition, Talibans, spent last 20 years doing nothing but war. War is their profession, its their life and they are damn good at it.<br>So yeah, by starting a war you're looking at a lot of possible casualties, on both sides. <br><br>You are right though, perhaps taking a passive approach is going to warrant more terracts over the next few years, and the same amount of casualties or higher, than the war would provide.<br><br>/shrug, the choice is a hard one to make, i am sure as hell glad i am not an US general or a pres atm <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usiggymk5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SiggyMk5</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 357<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/15/01 6:33:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www-scf.usc.edu/~rabiega/sigs/icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To the parties responsible for the 911 attacks:</span><hr size=1> More than the last 20 years... Hell, we trained Osama bin Laden and half the Taliban to fight the Soviets in Afghanistan quite some time ago... <p><p><center><img src="http://www-scf.usc.edu/~rabiega/sigs/april.jpg"><br><i>Sslanis Soulforge<br>It's not whose habitat it is, it's how hard you hit it</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ushadowknighttristan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShadowknightTristan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/15/01 9:45:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecomm